  "text": "For super-Hubble modes, kτ 1 , we can neglect terms proportional to k 2 . Furthermore, in the background branch under study, in the radiation era we have r 1, r −2Hr and m 2 β 1 a 2 r 0.48H Ω r /0.94 0.24 × 10 −2 H 2 0 = constant. Hence, in this regime, the last three terms in [CITATION_1] and (49) can be dropped and the two equations decouple. [CITATION_2] One of the main conclusions of Ref. [CITATION_3] is that during matter domination scalar perturbations do not exhibit exponential instabilities.",
